theorem compl_frontier_eq_interior_union_interior_compl
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    (frontier (A : Set X))ᶜ = interior A ∪ interior (Aᶜ) := by
  -- Start from the existing characterization of the complement of the frontier.
  have h₁ :=
    compl_frontier_eq_compl_closure_union_interior (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Replace `(closure A)ᶜ` with `interior (Aᶜ)`.
  have h₂ : (closure A : Set X)ᶜ = interior (Aᶜ) := by
    simpa using (interior_compl_eq_compl_closure (A := A)).symm
  -- Put everything together, reordering the union for the desired statement.
  simpa [h₂, Set.union_comm] using h₁

theorem interior_closure_inter_eq_inter_interior_of_closed
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : IsClosed A) (hB : IsClosed B) :
    interior (closure (A ∩ B)) = interior A ∩ interior B := by
  -- `A ∩ B` is closed because both `A` and `B` are closed.
  have hABclosed : IsClosed (A ∩ B) := hA.inter hB
  -- Hence its closure is itself.
  have h_closure : closure (A ∩ B) = A ∩ B := hABclosed.closure_eq
  -- Rewrite and use the distributivity of `interior` over intersections.
  simpa [h_closure, interior_inter]
